AGI -&nbsp; A heavy vehicle has taken fire along the A1 stretch between Valdarno and Arezzo and for this reason the closure of the highway in both directions of march, with queues that have exceeded 10 kilometers. The incident occurred at km 357 of Milan-Napoli and there are no injuries.
&nbsp;
"In the closed section the traffic is blocked with 11 km of tail towards Rome and 1 km of tail at the mandatory exit of Valdarno", read in a communication of Autostrade for Italy, "the distribution of water to users in the queue is in place".
<br> "In the direction of Florence, after the compulsory exit to Arezzo, where 4 km of tail were formed, continue on the SR 69 to Valdarno from where you can return to A1, reverse route for those traveling southward", continues the message. "For long walks we suggest to go out to Valdichiana, take the Siena-Bettolle SS326 junction towards Siena and return to Florence Impruneta. Reverse path for those traveling south." On the place are the staff of Autostrade for Italy and all the means of rescue.&nbsp;

